---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import ContactSurface from "../components/ContactSurface.astro";
import { SITE } from "../config/site";

const title = `Contact | ${SITE.name}`;
const description =
  "Contact CloudCostKit for estimate questions, calculator bugs, factual corrections, tool requests, and editorial feedback when a page needs review or a workflow looks wrong.";
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} canonicalPath="/contact">
  <section class="card hero">
    <h1>Contact</h1>
    <p>
      Use this page for estimate questions, calculator bugs, factual corrections, tool requests, and editorial
      feedback. The more concrete the input, the easier it is to review quickly.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card section prose">
    <h2 style="margin-top:0">Primary contact</h2>
    <p class="muted" style="margin:0">
      Use the contact module below if you want the most reliable path. It works even when the local mail app does not
      open automatically.
    </p>
    <ContactSurface email={SITE.email} label="Primary email" variant="full" />

    <h2 style="margin:18px 0 10px">Best reasons to contact us</h2>
    <ul class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0; padding-left:18px">
      <li>Report a calculator bug, broken input path, or output that looks directionally wrong.</li>
      <li>Point out a factual mistake, stale boundary explanation, or overlap between two pages.</li>
      <li>Ask for help understanding a provider pricing unit, validation step, or missing line item.</li>
      <li>Suggest a new calculator or guide when an existing workflow is clearly missing a real job.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="muted" style="margin:12px 0 0">Requests are triaged by type first: correction, calculator bug, estimate help, new topic request, or general site issue.</p>
    <p class="muted" style="margin:12px 0 0">Reports without a page URL, a concrete broken step, or a clear boundary problem are harder to action well.</p>

    <h2 style="margin:18px 0 10px">If you are asking for estimate help</h2>
    <ul class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0; padding-left:18px">
      <li>Include the page URL and the provider or region you care about.</li>
      <li>Share the measured driver you are using, such as requests per month, GB per month, retention days, or instance-hours.</li>
      <li>Say whether you want a baseline estimate, a peak scenario, or help understanding a billing boundary.</li>
      <li>If something looks wrong, include the exact inputs you used and the direction of the mismatch.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 style="margin:18px 0 10px">For correction requests, include:</h2>
    <ul class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0; padding-left:18px">
      <li>Include the page URL and the specific statement, output, or workflow step that looks wrong.</li>
      <li>Share the provider, region, unit, and any pricing rule involved if you know them.</li>
      <li>If the problem is reproducible, include the exact inputs or a screenshot of the issue.</li>
      <li>If the issue is about unclear wording or overlap with another page, link both pages.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="muted" style="margin:12px 0 0">If the issue depends on a provider rule, include the provider document or billing evidence you are using if possible.</p>

    <h2 style="margin:18px 0 10px">If you want a new tool or guide</h2>
    <ul class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0; padding-left:18px">
      <li>Describe the service and the key billable units, such as requests, GB processed, GB-month, or hours.</li>
      <li>List the line items that must be included or excluded, such as transfer, logs, replication, or add-ons.</li>
      <li>Share one realistic usage example so the default workflow can be designed around an actual planning task.</li>
      <li>If a similar page already exists, explain what is missing from it instead of only naming a new keyword.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 style="margin:18px 0 10px">What we can and cannot help with</h2>
    <ul class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0; padding-left:18px">
      <li><strong>We can</strong>: help model drivers, boundaries, units, and common missing line items.</li>
      <li><strong>We can</strong>: fix calculator bugs and improve wording, routing, and validation guidance.</li>
      <li><strong>We cannot</strong>: provide official quotes or guarantee a final bill because pricing tiers, regions, contracts, and rounding rules vary.</li>
      <li><strong>We cannot</strong>: access your provider billing data, so only share what you are comfortable sending.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 style="margin:18px 0 10px">Response expectations</h2>
    <p class="muted" style="margin:0">
      We aim to review clear correction or bug reports within a few business days. If your request is time-sensitive,
      add that context so it can be prioritized appropriately.
    </p>
    <p class="muted" style="margin:12px 0 0">
      Requests that include the page URL, provider, region, unit, and the exact part that looks wrong are much easier
      to review than generic "this seems off" messages.
    </p>
    <p class="muted" style="margin:12px 0 0">A strong report can lead to a direct correction, a clearer boundary explanation, a workflow rewrite, or lower prominence for a page that is no longer carrying its job well.</p>
    <p class="muted" style="margin:12px 0 0">Review does not guarantee that every suggestion will be adopted exactly as submitted.</p>

    <h2 style="margin:18px 0 10px">Related trust pages</h2>
    <ul class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0; padding-left:18px">
      <li><a href="/about/">About</a>: what the site is for and how pages earn publication.</li>
      <li><a href="/methodology/">Methodology</a>: how estimates should be built and validated.</li>
      <li><a href="/editorial-policy/">Editorial Policy</a>: how topics are reviewed, updated, and corrected.</li>
      <li><a href="/privacy-policy/">Privacy Policy</a>: how browser-side inputs and site usage are handled.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 style="margin:18px 0 10px">Privacy note</h2>
    <p class="muted" style="margin:0">
      Calculator inputs run in your browser. Some pages may store values in browser storage so your inputs persist
      between visits. See <a href="/privacy-policy/">Privacy Policy</a> and <a href="/cookie-notice/">Cookie Notice</a>.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
